# Cloudflare Pages SPA fallback. CF Pages serves static files first;
# any path without a matching prerendered file falls through to the
# rule below. Without this, `/lobby/<id>`, `/join/<code>` and any
# other non-indexable client route fell back to `/index.html` — the
# prerendered homepage — which flashed the homepage chrome on the
# browser before TanStack Router could route to the requested URL.
#
# Target `/_spa-shell` (an extension-less file, written by
# `scripts/prerender.ts`) rather than `/200.html` or `/_spa-shell/`:
# CF Pages canonicalizes URLs by stripping BOTH trailing `.html` and
# trailing `/`. Earlier attempts looped: `/200.html` 301'd to `/200`
# (no file → re-rewrite → 301 → …), `/_spa-shell/` 301'd to
# `/_spa-shell` (same shape). An extension-less file has nothing to
# strip, so CF serves it directly. `public/_headers` overrides the
# default `application/octet-stream` to `text/html`.
#
# Status `200` is a rewrite (URL stays put), not a redirect.
/*  /_spa-shell  200
